caption: This location is unfortunately consistently disappointing. Don't bother ordering pick-up, it will not be ready when you get there. Don't bother with delivery either, it only works about 50% of the time. The last time I went there they did not have any tuna salad. I'd be understanding of a small local restaurant being out of supplies, but I expect you to have all of your signature ingredients as a large chain. The food is fine, but management leaves much to be desired.

UPDATE: The store manager did finally get back to me, though a bit of comical exchange ensued.  I was refunded the cost of the order, only 7 days later.  Still waiting on that salad and sandwich I ordered last week, and don't forget the Mac!  Seriously though, I ordered through their website for delivery 2 hrs prior to when I wanted it delivered, called once after an hour past my delivery window and was promptly hung up on.  Still waiting to hear back on the "Submit your feedback" I sent over.  I'm about ready to call my bank and file a fraud claim to get this resolved.  Look, it's hard times all around Potbelly, if you can't take delivery orders, that's okay.  Just disable the option and ask for pickup only.   People will be more understanding with that response than taking an order, charging them, and not delivering on that order.  Now that's called fraud.

By the way when you see the supposed owner reply, please note below a uber driver complained and the owners response was like they ate there.. so they cant even show concern on their bad review replies... stay away!! half the time the sandwiches are worse than you make at home

The service at this location is absolutely terrible!! Every time I go in there, no one seems to want to help you! I work down the street from this location. I like the food, so I have changed my method to order online and pick it up instead, just to avoid all of the employees as much as possible. This particular time, I walk in to pick up my ONLINE ORDER. The cashier literally makes eye contact with me, and then walks away to the back. All of the other employees are busy. I'm waiting there, then as soon as the phone starts ringing, he runs from the back to the register to pick up that phone call. (Mind you, they forgot to give a whole sandwich to a delivery order-phone call). After he hangs up the phone, he then proceeds to assist the customer who just got done finishing getting their sandwich made. I ask him if I should go wait in line and tells me that I don't have to wait, but I have to wait until he's done with that customer. I was standing there first!! Am I invisible? Am I not a customer? Do I not deserve the same service? What is the point of an online order and stating that we don't have to wait in line, but yet, I still have to wait? This is honestly the WORST Potbelly location that I go to. Definitely do not recommend this location!

I was just at this Potbelly location about 3 minutes ago and I can definitely say I will never be back. First off, that potbelly is pure mess. None of their sandwich breads or knifes and other utensils are organized. The place looks completely and utterly cluttered and to be honest, it’s not pleasant to look at. All of the workers, including the “manager” have the worst attitudes with no enjoyment of working. I was never even greeted with a hello, how disappointing. When it was my time to pay, I ordered two side soups and was given my soup, two spoons, and a bag of crackers. Not even a bag was offered to carry all those things in, and when I finally asked for a bag, the worker literally threw one at me. I was baffled and told him that he should bag my soups for me instead of literally lunging the bag at my face. When I confronted him about throwing the bag at me, he yells right at my face and starts calling me a pathological liar and that I was a bull faced liar. I was shocked that a worker would speak with such inappropriate appalling slurs to a customer. I was not satisfied with the service the Irving Park Potbelly provided. If you want a bag thrown and your face, and uncleanliness language spoken towards you, please feel free and stop by their location because they seriously know how to make your day go from good to bad.
